---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Our Work | Belvedere Decks"
  description="Completed composite deck projects in Maryland: before-and-after transformations and the framing photos most builders never show you."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Our Work</p>
      <h1>The work, documented honestly.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        Every project is photographed at three moments: before, during the frame
        inspection, and finished. Most builders only show you the third one.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why we photograph the frame</h2>
      <p>
        The mid-build photo is the one that matters. It shows the parts of your deck
        you'll never see again once the boards go down: the flashing at the house, the
        steel connectors, the footings that passed county inspection. We post ours
        because we're proud of them.
      </p>

      <!-- GALLERY: real project photos only. No stock images, no placeholder projects,
           no AI-generated shots. Each entry: before, framing, finished hero, town,
           service line, board/rail spec. First entries: Hammil (Boyds), Bonaparte. -->
      <div class="notice">
        <strong>Current projects are under construction.</strong> Finished galleries land
        here as each build completes: before-and-after pairs, the frame photos, and the
        full specifications. Check back soon, or
        <a href="/estimate">ask to see work in progress</a>.
      </div>

      <p><a class="btn primary" href="/estimate">Get a Free Estimate</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
